definition: a tangible and visible entity, express or raise an objection or protest or criticism or express dissent
details:
noun
- a tangible and visible entity
= synonyms: physical object
- the focus of cognitions or feelings
= example: the focus of cognitions or feelings
- the goal intended to be attained, and which is believed to be attainable
= example: the goal intended to be attained, and which is believed to be attainable
= synonyms: aim, objective, target
- (computing) a discrete item that provides a description of virtually anything known to a computer
= example: (computing) a discrete item that provides a description of virtually anything known to a computer
- (grammar) a constituent that is acted upon
= example: (grammar) a constituent that is acted upon
verb
- express or raise an objection or protest or criticism or express dissent
= example: express or raise an objection or protest or criticism or express dissent
- be averse to or express disapproval of
= example: be averse to or express disapproval of
